application_type_full: Outline planning permission: Some matters reserved

open_spaces_details.description: The existing building footprint of the leisure centre is approximately 3,950sqm but including the car park this totals 10,672sqm. The proposed built footprint with the new leisure centre and illustrative housing scheme in place totals 13,877sqm. There is therefore an encroachment of 3,205sqm built footprint on the MOL when compared to the existing previously developed land.

decision_conditions: The full planning permission element of the approved development shall be begun not later than the expiration of three years from the date of this permission.
Reason: In order to comply with Section 91 of the Town and Country Planning Act 1990 (as amended).

| The reserved matters application for the outline planning permission element of the approved development shall be made not later than the expiration of three years beginning with the date of the grant of outline planning permission, and the development to which the permission relates shall be begun not later than the expiration of two years from the final approval of the reserved matters or, in the case of approval on different dates, the final approval of the last such matter to be approved.
Reason: In order to comply with the Section 92 of the Town and Country Planning Act 1990 (as amended).

Reason: For the avoidance of doubt and in the interest of proper planning. | The outline planning permission element of the approved development shall not commence until the reserved matters of appearance, landscaping, access and parking, layout, and scale have been approved by the Local Planning Authority. The reserved matters application shall be in accordance with the drawing numbers and supporting documents listed in Condition 3. The outline planning permission element of the approved development shall be implemented in accordance with the approved reserved matters application, unless otherwise agreed with the Local Planning Authority through the submission of a planning application.
The information on access and parking to be submitted and approved by the LPA as part of the reserved matters shall include:
-	Details of the proposed access points and car / cycle parking provision
-	A review of the trip generation for the residential units for all modes
-	A review of the traffic modelling with TfL and whether this is needed at this stage, especially if the leisure centre is operational

Reason: To ensure the Local Planning Authority is satisfied with the details of the reserved matters for the outline planning permission element of the approved development, in accordance with Articles 5, 6 and 7 of the Town and Country Planning (General Development Management Procedure) Order 2015.

| The first phase of the approved development (excluding demolition, site clearance and ground works) shall not commence until a phasing plan for the implementation of the approved development has been submitted to and approved in writing by the Local Planning Authority. The phasing plan shall include details of all building works within each phase of the development (including timeframes for their implementation). The development shall proceed in accordance with the approved phasing plan, unless otherwise agreed with the Local Planning Authority through the submission of a planning application.
Reason: To ensure an appropriate phasing of the approved development.

| Notwithstanding the approved drawings and supporting documents, details of materials and finishes to be used for all external building surfaces and samples shall be submitted to and approved in writing by the Local Planning Authority for each individual phase, prior to commencement (excluding demolition, site clearance and ground works) of the relevant phase. Each phase of the development shall be carried out in accordance with these approved details and retained as such thereafter.

Reason: To ensure that the materials harmonise with the surroundings, in accordance with Policies D3 and D4 of the London Plan (2021), Policies 7.4 and 7B of the Ealing Development Management DPD (2013) and Policy DAA of Ealing's draft Local Plan (Reg. 22).

| Notwithstanding the approved drawings and supporting documents, details of hard and soft landscaping, boundary treatments and outdoor furniture for that particular phase shall be submitted to and approved in writing by the Local Planning Authority, prior to occupation of that phase of the development. The approved details shall be implemented and retained as such thereafter.

Reason: To ensure appropriate hard and soft landscaping, boundary treatments and outdoor furniture, in the interests of the visual character and appearance of the area and public realm, in accordance with Policies D3, D4 and D8 of the London Plan (2021), Policies 7.4 and 7B of the Ealing Development Management DPD (2013) and Policy DAA of Ealing's draft Local Plan (Reg. 22).

| Prior to occupation of each individual phase of the approved development, a Landscape Management Plan (which shall include a programme for its implementation) for the relevant phase, shall be submitted to and approved in writing by the Local Planning Authority. The landscaping shall be carried out and thereafter managed in accordance with the approved details for the lifetime of the development, unless otherwise agreed with the Local Planning Authority through the submission of a planning application.

Reason: To ensure appropriately landscaped amenity space and public realm, in accordance with Policies D3, D4 and D8 of the London Plan (2021), Policies 7.4 and 7B of the Ealing Development Management DPD (2013) and Policy DAA of Ealing's draft Local Plan (Reg. 22).

| Prior to occupation of each individual phase of the approved development, details of construction, specification and maintenance of the green roofs, shall be submitted to and approved in writing by the Local Planning Authority for the relevant phase. The green roofs shall be implemented and managed in accordance with these approved details for the lifetime of the development, unless otherwise agreed with the Local Planning Authority through the submission of a planning application.
Reason: To improve the natural environment and biodiversity, in accordance with Policies G5 and G6 of the London Plan (2021) and Policy 5.11 of the Ealing Development Management DPD (2013).

| Prior to commencement of the relevant phase of the approved development (excluding demolition, site clearance and groundworks), a Biodiversity Gain Plan (which shall include a programme for its implementation) for that particular phase, shall be submitted to and approved in writing by the Local Planning Authority. The development shall be carried out in accordance with these approved details and retained as such thereafter.
Reason: To ensure that the biodiversity gain objective is met, in accordance with Schedule 7A of the Town and Country Planning Act (1990) and Policy G6 of the London Plan (2021).

| Prior to occupation of each individual phase of the approved development, the greening measures to achieve an Urban Greening Factor (UGF) score of 0.54 for that phase shall be fully implemented. The implemented greening measures shall be retained and adequately maintained thereafter.

Reason: To improve the natural environment and biodiversity, in accordance with Policies G5 and G6 of the London Plan (2021) and Policies 5.10 and 5.11 of the Ealing Development Management DPD (2013).
| The roof of the buildings shall not be used for any purpose other than as a means of escape in emergency or for maintenance of the buildings.

Reason: To safeguard the amenities of future occupiers, neighbouring properties and the area generally, in accordance with Policy 7B of the Ealing Development Management DPD (2013) and Policy DAA of Ealing's draft Local Plan (Reg. 22).
| 10 per cent of the approved residential units shall be designed and constructed to meet Building Regulation requirement M4(3), with the remaining units meeting the requirement of M4(2).
Reason: To provide accessible housing, in accordance with Policy D7 of the London Plan (2021).

| Prior to occupation of each individual phase of the approved development, the passenger lifts, where proposed shall be installed for the relevant phase and made fully operational. The installed passenger lifts shall be permanently retained and maintained in good working order thereafter.
Reason: To provide adequate access to all floors, in accordance with Policy D5 of the London Plan (2021).

| Prior to occupation of the approved leisure centre, details of the delivery, management, and maintenance of the public toilets and changing places facility shall be submitted to and approved in writing by the Local Planning Authority. The development shall be carried out in accordance with these approved details and retained as such thereafter.
Reason: To ensure the provision of public toilets and changing places facility, in accordance with Policy S6 of the London Plan (2021).

| Prior to occupation of the first phase of the approved development, details of the provision and future management of free drinking water at the development site shall be submitted to and approved in writing by the Local Planning Authority. The development shall be carried out in accordance with these approved details and retained as such thereafter.
Reason: To ensure the provision of free drinking water, in accordance with Policy D8 of the London Plan (2021).

| (a) The approved leisure centre shall be constructed and operated in strict accordance with the details and recommendations set out in the 'SD15A: Leisure Centre Fire Safety Statement April 2024' and 'SD15B: Leisure Centre Fire Safety Strategy April 2024', unless otherwise agreed in writing by the Local Planning Authority through the submission of a planning application.

(b) Notwithstanding the approved drawings and supporting documents, a Fire Safety Statement and Strategy for the approved residential development shall be submitted to and approved in writing by the Local Planning Authority, prior to commencement of the approved residential development. The approved residential development shall be constructed and operated in accordance with the approved Fire Safety Statement and Strategy, unless otherwise agreed in writing by the Local Planning Authority through the submission of a planning application.
Reason: To provide adequate fire safety, in accordance with Policy D12 of the London Plan (2021).

| Each residential building shall obtain a 'Secured by Design' Accreditation prior to first occupation of that building. The works to the Leisure centre would be consulted with the Metropolitan Police The development shall only be carried out in accordance with the approved details and maintained thereafter.

Reason: To ensure the safety of future users, in accordance with Policy D11 of the London Plan (2021), Policy 7.3 of the Ealing Development Management DPD (2013) and Sections 8 and 12 of the NPPF (2024).

| Notwithstanding the approved drawings and supporting documents, a Construction Management Plan shall be submitted for each phase of the development and approved in writing by the Local Planning Authority, prior to commencement of the relevant phase of the development (excluding demolition, site clearance and groundworks).The development shall not be implemented other than in accordance with the approved details through the construction period. Details shall include:
a) control measures for:
- noise and vibration (according to Approved CoP BS 5228-1 and -2:2009+A1:2014),
- dust (according to Supplementary Planning Guidance by the GLA (2014) for The Control of Dust and Emissions during Construction and Demolition),
- lighting ('Guidance Note 01/20 For The Reduction Of Obtrusive Light' by the Institution   of Lighting Professionals),
- delivery locations,
- hours of work and all associated activities audible beyond the site boundary restricted to 0800-1800hrs Mondays to Fridays and 0800 -1300 Saturdays (except no work on public holidays),
- neighbour liaison, notifications to interested parties and
- public display of contact details including accessible phone numbers for persons responsible for the site works for the duration of the works
b) details related to:
- pre-construction highway survey - Leisure element,
- traffic management,

- construction lorry route from the main distributor roads and the number of constructions related vehicles, which would be travelling to the application site.  A drawing showing signing for the construction vehicles is also required,
- key dates of various stages and all the emergency contacts during construction,
- abnormal load delivery vehicle routes and dates of these deliveries, and
- swept path envelopes for construction lorries, HGV's and crane vehicles.

Reason: To ensure that the amenity of occupiers of neighbouring properties and the area generally is not adversely affected by noise, vibration, dust, lighting or other emissions from the site, in accordance with Policies D14, SI 1, SI 2, T4 and T7 of the London Plan (2021), Policy 7A of the Ealing Development Management DPD (2013), Policy DAA of Ealing's draft Local Plan (Reg. 22), the NPPF (2024) and SPG10 Noise and Vibration. | Notwithstanding the approved drawings and supporting documents:
(a) a Leisure Centre Travel Plan shall be submitted to and approved in writing by the Local Planning Authority prior to occupation of the approved leisure centre; and
(b) a Residential Travel Plan shall be submitted to and approved in writing by the Local Planning Authority at reserve matter stage, prior to occupation of the approved residential development.

Each Travel Plan shall be prepared in accordance with the Transport for London Travel Plan Guidance and Ealing's Sustainable Transport for New Development SPD in use at the time of its preparation. Each phase of the development shall be carried out in accordance with the approved Travel Plans in respect of that phase.

Reason: To encourage sustainable transport and reduce traffic and congestion, in accordance with Policies T1, T2, T4, T5 and T6 of the London Plan (2021) and Ealing's SPD 'Sustainable Transport for New Development'.

| Notwithstanding the approved drawings and supporting documents, a Delivery and Servicing Plan for the relevant phase of the development shall be submitted to and approved in writing by the Local Planning Authority, prior to occupation of that individual phase of the development. The development shall operate in strict accordance with the approved details in perpetuity.

Reason: To ensure adequate highway safety and safeguard the amenities of future occupiers, neighbouring properties and the area generally, in accordance with Policies T3, T4, T7 and D14 of the London Plan (2021), Policy 7A of the Ealing Development Management DPD (2013) and Policy DAA of Ealing's draft Local Plan (Reg. 22).

| Prior to occupation of each individual phase of the approved development, details of cycle storage shall be submitted to and approved in writing by the Local Planning Authority for the relevant phase. The cycle parking shall be provided and retained for the lifetime of the development.
Reason: To ensure adequate cycle storage, in accordance with Policy T6 of the London Plan (2021).

| 20 per cent of all car parking spaces shall be equipped with active electric vehicle charging provision (if there is sufficient electricity supply from the electrical grid), and the remaining car parking spaces shall be equipped with passive electric vehicle charging provision. This provision shall be permanently retained thereafter and shall only be altered for maintenance or upgrades.
Reason: To provide adequate electric car charging provision, in accordance with Policy T6 of the London Plan (2021).

| Prior to occupation of the relevant phase of the approved development, a Waste Management Plan for that particular phase, shall be submitted to and approved in writing by the Local Planning Authority. The development shall be carried out in accordance with these approved details and retained as such thereafter, unless otherwise agreed with the Local Planning Authority through the submission of a planning application.
Reason: To ensure adequate waste management, in accordance with Policy SI 7 of the London Plan (2021).

| Prior to commencement of each phase of the approved development (excluding initial site clearance and ground works), details to demonstrate the provision of sufficient ducting space for full fibre connectivity infrastructure within the relevant phase, shall be submitted to and approved in writing by the Local Planning Authority. The development shall be carried out in accordance with these approved details and retained as such thereafter.
Reason: To promote digital connectivity infrastructure, in accordance with Policy SI 6 of London Plan (2021).

| The development hereby approved shall not be occupied until refuse and recycling storage within a secure enclosure has been provided in accordance with the designated location identified in the approved drawings listed under condition 3 and in accordance with the Local Planning Authority Standards and has been fully implemented and made available for use. These facilities shall permanently retained thereafter.
Reason: To ensure the provision of satisfactory facilities for the storage of refuse and recycling material, in accordance with policy SI 8 of the London Plan (2021).

| Prior to the commencement of the development relevant phase of the development (excluding demolition, site clearance and groundworks), a Ventilation Strategy Report shall be submitted to and approved by the Local Planning Authority. The report should contain details for providing fresh air ventilation for the development, air intake should be located away from sources of local pollution as specified in the Ventilation: Approved Document F, Volume 1: Dwellings. The report shall also include the following information: a) Details and locations of the ventilation intake locations of all floors b) Details and locations of ventilation extracts locations of all floors The maintenance and cleaning of the systems shall be undertaken regularly in accordance with manufacturer specifications and shall be the responsibility of the primary owner of the property. Approved details shall be fully implemented prior to the occupation/use of the development and thereafter permanently retained and maintained.

Reason: To minimise exposure to existing poor air quality, and provide a suitable internal living environment for future occupiers, in accordance with policy SI 1 of the London Plan 2021, policy 1.1(j) of the Ealing Development Strategy 2026 DPD (2012); and policy 7A of the Ealing Development Management DPD (2013).

| Prior to commencement of any construction works onsite, an Air Quality and Dust Management Plan (AQDMP) shall be submitted for the approval of the Local Planning Authority. The AQDMP will be based on the findings of Air Quality (Dust) Risk Assessment provided in the Air Quality Assessment report titled "GURNELL LEISURE CENTRE PLANNING APPLICATION SD05: AIR QUALITY ASSESSMENT" dated April 2024. The AQDMP will provide a scheme for air pollution mitigation measures based on the findings of the Air quality report.
The plan shall include:
a)Dust Management Plan for Construction Phase

Direct access to air quality monitoring data will be always provided and the air quality monitors shall be maintained onsite until first occupation of the development hereby approved. The Air Quality Dust Management Plan shall be implemented on commencement of any construction works on site and the site shall be managed in accordance with the approved plan for the duration of the construction.

Reason: In the interests of the amenity of adjoining occupiers and to minimise particulate matter associated with construction works in accordance with policies 1.1 (e) (f) (j) of the Ealing Development (Core) Strategy 2012, policy 7Aof the Ealing Development Management Development Plan (2013) and policy SI1 of the London Plan (2021); and National Planning Policy Framework (2024).

| All Non-Road Mobile Machinery (NRMM) of net power of 37kW and up to and including 560kW used during the course of the demolition, site preparation and construction phases shall comply with the emission standards as published on the NRMM Website (https://nrmm.london/). Unless it complies with the standards set out on the website, no NRMM shall be on site, at any time, whether in use or not, without the prior written consent of the local planning authority. The developer shall keep an up to date list of all NRMM used during the demolition, site preparation and construction phases of the development on the online register at https://nrmm.london/

Reason: To safeguard adjoining occupiers of the development against unacceptable noise, disturbance and emissions, policies 1.1(j) of the Ealing Development (Core) Strategy (2012), Local Variation policy 3.5 and policy 7A of Ealing's Development Management DPD (2013) and policy SI1 of the London Plan(2021); and National Planning Policy Framework (2024).

| No diesel or petrol generators will be installed onsite without prior approval from the Local Planning Authority. Any new proposed diesel or petrol generators should demonstrate compliance with a minimum NOx emissions standard of 150mg/Nm-3 (at 5% O2) and must be submitted and approved in writing by the Local Planning Authority. The details must include the results of NOx emissions testing of the diesel or petrol fuelled generator units by an accredited laboratory, emissions concentrations expressed at specific reference conditions for temperature, pressure, oxygen and moisture content under normal operating conditions. Where any combustion plant does not meet the relevant standard, it should not be operated without the fitting of suitable NOx abatement equipment or technology. Evidence of installation shall be required where secondary abatement is required to meet the NOx Emission standard 150mg/Nm-3 (at 5% O2). The emergency plant and generators hereby permitted may be operated only for essential testing, except when required in an emergency situation.

Reason: To ensure LA meets its obligations to deliver air quality objectives for NO2 in accordance with London Local Air Quality Management (LLAQM), and to limit PM2.5 (fine particulates) to safeguard public health and well-being and external amenity of nearby sensitive receptors.

| a) Prior to construction completion and occupation, the Leisure Centre Development shall implement and maintain, and in the case of energy generation equipment confirm as operational, the approved measures to achieve an overall sitewide reduction in regulated CO2 emissions of at least 35.43% (equating to 32.1 tonnes of CO2 per year) beyond Building Regulations Part L 2021 and using SAP 10.2 emission factors. These CO2 savings shall be achieved through the Lean, Clean, Green Energy Hierarchy as detailed in the approved Energy Statement prepared by Anderson Green (Leisure Centre) in March 2024 (v1) including:

i.	Lean, energy efficiency design measures to achieve an annual reduction of at least 9.05% equating to at least 8.2 tonnes in regulated carbon dioxide (CO2) emissions over BR Part L 2021 (using SAP 10.2 conversion factors).

ii.	Green, renewable energy equipment including the incorporation of photovoltaic panels with a combined total capacity of approximately 154 kWp, and Air Source Heat Pumps to achieve an annual reduction of at least 26.38%, equating to 23.9 tonnes, in regulated carbon dioxide (CO2) emissions over Part L 2021 (using SAP 10.2 emission factors).

iii.	Seen, heat and electric meters installed to monitor the performance of the PV and the carbon efficiency (SCOP) of the Air Source Heat Pump systems (including the heat generation and the electrical parasitic loads of the heat pumps), in line with the Council's monitoring requirements.
